<p><em>How does it work?</em> When you create an account on Mastodon, you create an account on the website you currently are visiting. For example, here you are on <u>mastodon.org.uk</u>. That is your instance.
<br><br>
You will notice after log in two different timelines, the Local and the Federated.<br>
The local timeline is all the public toots of all our local users ( the one who registered on mastodon.org.uk and use it to access the Mastodon federation ).<br>
The federated timeline adds the public toots of all the users that our local users are following in other servers/</p>

<p><em>Need to know users</em> <br>
	<a href="https://mastodon.org.uk/@xvilo">@xvilo</a> Is the maintainer of this instance.<br>
	<a href="https://mastodon.org.uk/@status">@STATUS</a> Gives you information about this instance.<br>
	<a href="https://mastodon.org.uk/@userscount">@userscount</a> Gives us detailed info about users and toots.<br>
</p>

<p><em>Bots on this instance</em> <br>
	<a href="https://mastodon.org.uk/@status">@STATUS</a> Gives us an automated heads up when there is a <a href="https://github.com/xvilo/Mastodon-Update-Notifier">new Mastodon Version available</a>.<br>
	<a href="https://mastodon.org.uk/@userscount">@userscount</a> Gives us detailed info about users and toots. <a href="https://github.com/josefkenny/usercount">Source on Github</a><br>
	<a href="https://mastodon.org.uk/@bigben">@bigben</a> Toots the time. <a href="https://github.com/cablespaghetti/bigben">Source on Github</a>. Maintained by <a href="https://mastodon.org.uk/@followthesam">@followthesam</a><br><br>
	Bots <em>are welcome here</em> but please not that bots will be silenced when posting too much (e.g. flooding local timeline). If you have a bot, please contact me <a href="https://mastodon.org.uk/@xvilo">(@xvilo)</a>. I can add it to the list. <br>
	Bots <em>will be banned</em> if they post inappropriate content or if I <a href="https://mastodon.org.uk/@xvilo">(@xvilo)</a> get many complaints about it. 
</p></p>
